Barcelona Extends Lead Over Manchester Utd 3-1 in Champions League Final

-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 
2011-05-28T20:16:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-28/barcelona-extends-lead-over-manchester-utd-3-1-in-champions-league-final.html
Barcelona took a 3-1 lead over
 Manchester United  as  David Villa  took advantage of confusion in
the English champion’s penalty area to score in the 69th minute.  Lionel Messi, who had given the Spanish league champion the
lead in the 54th minute, took the ball in from the corner of
United’s half and lost possession, but United failed to clear.
The ball came to Villa, who hooked a shot past Edwin van der
Sar.  Messi’s goal was the Argentine’s 12th goal in 13 matches.
United had tied the match in the 34th minute on  Wayne Rooney ’s
strike at London’s Wembley Stadium.  Rooney exchanged passes with Ryan Giggs, getting the ball
back just inside the Spanish champion’s penalty area and curling
a shot into the net. Barcelona had taken a 1-0 lead in the 27th
minute when  Pedro Rodriguez  struck a right-footed effort past
United goalkeeper Edwin van der Sar.  The winner will claim its fourth European title.  United coach Alex Ferguson decided not to include striker
Dimitar Berbatov in the squad, using Michael Owen on the bench
instead, while Barcelona’s Pep Guardiola kept defender Carles
Puyol among his subs. Berbatov had 21 goals in England’s Premier
League this season, tying him as top scorer with Manchester  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
